        introduction: "The taxi transfer from Toulouse-Blagnac Airport to Auch takes you in under an hour to the historic capital of Gascony, the legendary land of musketeers and fine living. Auch, capital of the Gers department, is a characterful town perched on a promontory overlooking the Gers valley with sweeping views towards the Pyrenees on clear days. The Sainte-Marie Cathedral, a flamboyant Gothic masterpiece, houses 18 Renaissance stained-glass windows by Arnaut de Moles, considered among France's finest, and 113 intricately carved oak choir stalls depicting over 1,500 biblical and mythological figures. The monumental staircase of 370 steps descends from the cathedral to the riverbank past the statue of d'Artagnan, the legendary Gascon musketeer. The Gers is famed for its gastronomy — foie gras, duck confit, armagnac brandy — and for having France's highest life expectancy. From the airport where Airbus aircraft are assembled just metres from the terminal, the drive to Auch crosses rolling, timeless Gascon countryside.",
        itineraire: "From the airport, the driver takes the N124 expressway heading directly west towards Auch. The road crosses Colomiers and the Airbus aerospace zone before quickly reaching the Gers countryside. The route passes through L'Isle-Jourdain, a medieval bastide on the Save river, then crosses the rolling Gascon landscapes of cultivated hillsides, oak copses and small villages with canal-tile roofs. The dual carriageway is toll-free and provides a fast, comfortable ride. Auch is approached from the north with a descent into the Gers valley offering a first glimpse of the upper town dominated by the massive cathedral towers. The driver drops you at the historic centre, the monumental staircase, the station or your accommodation.",
        conseils: "The N124 expressway is entirely toll-free, making this an economical transfer. The road is generally smooth with only one possible slowdown through L'Isle-Jourdain at rush hours. If your flight arrives in the late afternoon, you may enjoy a stunning sunset over the Gascon hills during the drive, particularly beautiful in autumn. For food lovers, the Gers is packed with farm-restaurants and foie gras and armagnac producers the driver can recommend. If visiting in summer, Auch hosts the Eclats de Voix festival and lively evening markets on Place de la Liberation. The Sunday morning market is one of south-west France's finest, with artisan foie gras, local produce and vintage armagnacs.",
